{meta: title How Many}
{meta: artist Jim Reeves}
{meta: composer Hal Blair and Howard Barnes}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]If all the guys you ever knew
[F]Were standing here in front of you
[C]I wonder just how many there would [G7]be
[C]If everyone you ever kissed
[F]Was put on paper in a list
[C]I wonder just how [G7]many there would [C]be
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]You must have kissed a million for everywhere we [C]go
[D7]You seem so well acquainted
[G7]The way they smile and say hello
[C]If I could count their broken hearts
[F]Like I would have if we should part
[C]I wonder just how [G7]many there would [C]be
{end_of_verse}

